g.text: Shows the final executable memory layout with PT_LOAD segments: text segment (RX) containing .text and .rodata, data segment (RW) containing .data and .bss, with page alignment boundaries.

ul.li: PT_LOAD: Program header type for loadable segments
Page Alignment: Segments aligned to system page boundaries
Contiguous sections: Sections within same segment are contiguous in memory

div.p: .bss Uninitialized/zero-initialized data Read-Write (RW) (No space in file, zero-filled at load)
